				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Today in Small Business: &#8216;Google Dorking&#8217;</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Gene Marks			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-08-29T16:40:40+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">August 29, 2014 12:40 pm</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">August 29, 2014 12:40 pm</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/29/today-in-small-business-google-dorking/" data-title="Today in Small Business: &#8216;Google Dorking&#8217;" data-description="Why Bo Jackson is suing a small meat packager. Fifteen strategies to help independent retailers. And what the S.B.A. could do to &quot;unfreeze small-business credit.&quot; ">
				<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad"></div>
				<div id="MiddleLeft" class="ad middle-left-ad nocontent robots-nocontent"></div>
				</div><div class="inlineModule"><div class="entry"><h6 class="kicker"><a href="//boss.blogs.nytimes.com/category/dashboard/">Dashboard</a></h6><p class="summary">A daily roundup of small-business developments.</p></div></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Whatâs affecting me, my clients and other small-business owners today.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Economy</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Recent economic data is <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/29/business/us-economy-grew-at-brisk-rate-in-second-quarter.html?p">pointing</a> up.</li>
<li>All of the Federal Reserveâs regional surveys <a href="//www.calculatedriskblog.com/2014/08/regional-manufacturing-surveys-suggest.html">showed expansion</a> in August.</li>
<li>Yet a poll indicates <a href="//abcnews.go.com/Business/wireStory/survey-americans-pessimism-economy-grown-25154830#.U_">pessimism</a> on the economy has grown.</li>
<li>Major seed companies donât <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/big-seed-makers-unlikely-to-cut-prices-despite-u-s-farming-slump-1409242542?">plan to cut prices</a> for the next growing season despite sliding corn and soybean prices.</li>
<li>United States <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/08/29/business/energy-environment/shale-oil-in-texas-keeps-gas-prices-affordable.html">refinery production has reached record highs</a> and supply depots are full â meaning lower prices at the pump.</li>
<li>Lending for construction <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/lending-for-construction-grows-4-in-2nd-quarter-1409247736?mod=r">grew 4 percent</a> in the second quarter.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>The Law</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Supreme Court will take up a case that involves<a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/state-licensing-boards-under-fire-from-within-1409184515?tesla=y&amp;mod=djemSB_h&amp;mg=reno64-wsj&amp;url=//online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052970203937904580118060533093160.html?mod=djemSB_h"> the proliferation of state licenses</a>.</li>
<li>Here is why Bo Jackson <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-08-28/why-bo-jackson-won-t-stop-suing-a-small-arizona-meat-packager">wonât stop suing</a> a small meat packager.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Online</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Businesses should be on the lookout for &#8220;<a href="//www.businessinsider.com/term-of-the-day-google-dorking-2014-8?">Google Dorking,</a>&#8221; which is a term for the use of advanced search techniques by malicious hackers looking for stuff that companies didn&#8217;t mean to put online.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span id="more-88226"></span><br />
<strong>Retail</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s how <a href="//www.washingtoncitypaper.com/articles/46224/the-dives-of-others-how-to-open-a-new-old-bar/">to open</a> a new bar that feels old.</li>
<li>Here are 15 <a href="//www.inc.com/kimberly-weisul/15-strategies-for-independent-retailers.html">strategies</a> to help independent retailers stand up to the likes of Amazon and Walmart.</li>
<li>An online retailer says it will <a href="//consumerist.com/2014/08/27/online-retailer-will-fine-you-250-if-you-even-threaten-to-complain-about-purchase/">fine customers $250</a> if they threaten to complain about a purchase.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Employees</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The California Supreme Court has <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/danielfisher/2014/08/28/california-supreme-court-rejects-obama-administration-theory-on-franchise-employees/">rejected the idea</a> that franchise companies are the employers of workers who are hired, fired and managed by independent store owners.</li>
<li><a href="//www.npr.org/blogs/money/2014/08/27/343415569/whos-in-the-office-the-american-workday-in-one-graph?">This graph</a> sums up the American workday.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Management</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Here&#8217;s why Motorola no longer <a href="//www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/September-2014/What-Happened-to-Motorola/?">dominates the telecom industry</a>.</li>
<li>Here&#8217;s how <a href="//www.adweek.com/news/advertising-branding/how-once-cool-urban-outfitters-lost-its-mojo-159766">once-cool</a> Urban Outfitters lost its mojo.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Marketing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A grocery chains asks <a href="//twentytwowords.com/6-year-old-brit-criticizes-grocery-chains-label-look-at-the-new-one-they-let-him-draw/">a 6-year-old</a> to design its label.</li>
<li>Here are three ways to <a href="//blog.referralcandy.com/2014/08/26/3-ways-acquiring-customers-scale-infographic/">acquire customers</a> who are not just one-offs.</li>
<li>The brand manager of a vacuum cleaner tries to show <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/exec-eats-off-floor-to-sell-vacuum-cleaner/">how good</a> the product is at cleaning germs by eating off a subway floor.</li>
<li>If you <a href="//blog.brazencareerist.com/2014/08/28/email-tips-want-response-never-start-message-like/?">want a response</a> to an email, don&#8217;t start it like this.</li>
<li>A publicist <a href="//www.blackenterprise.com/small-business/labor-love-teia-harris-explains-her-love-publicity/">explains her love</a> of publicity.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Finance</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A former chief of the Small Business Administration thinks the government <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/hbsworkingknowledge/2014/08/28/government-can-do-more-to-unfreeze-small-business-credit/">could be doing more</a> to unfreeze small-business credit.</li>
<li>A new tech investment fund backed by Peyton and Eli Manning and Carmelo Anthony <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/darrenheitner/2014/08/28/seatgeeks-35-million-raise-includes-superstar-investors-peyton-manning-carmelo-anthony-and-nas/">invests $35 million</a> in a ticket search engine.</li>
<li>Andreessen Horowitz and Norwest Venture Partners <a href="//venturebeat.com/2014/08/28/iot-startup-ifttt-takes-in-30m-to-get-your-apps-talking-to-each-other/">invest $30 million</a> in a new Internet of Things start-up that wants to connect your online social interactions.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Opportunities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>An entrepreneur has found an opportunity <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x-e9j8YM9dI">making artisan soaps</a> with olive oil from trees surrounding her home.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the Country</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Appleâs <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/apple-flagship-store-fills-with-protestors/#ft">flagship store</a> in San Francisco fills with protesters accusing the company of underpaying contract workers.</li>
<li>The price of a big Brooklyn laundry site <a href="//www.crainsnewyork.com/article/20140828/REAL_ESTATE/140829840/price-of-big-bklyn-laundry-site-doubles-in-year">doubled</a> in a year.</li>
<li>A bike business <a href="//www.bizjournals.com/albany/news/2014/08/28/plaines-bike-business-growing-in-schenectady-malta.html?p">expands in Schenectady</a>, N.Y.</li>
<li>The Port of Long Beach has <a href="//www.marinelink.com/news/business-raises-beach375881.aspx">set a higher goal</a> to buy goods and services from small businesses.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Around the World</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>China&#8217;s toilet paper <a href="//www.forbes.com/sites/shuchingjeanchen/2014/08/28/chinas-toilet-paper-makers-flush-with-cash/">makers have plenty</a> of cash.</li>
<li>British retailers are more <a href="//www.theguardian.com/business/2014/aug/29/retailers-most-optimistic-12-years-august-sales-surge-consumer-confidence">optimistic</a> than they have been in the last 12 years. Still, according to <a href="//www.csmonitor.com/USA/DC-Decoder/Decoder-Voices/2014/0828/Britain-poorer-than-all-US-states-except-Mississippi">this calculation</a>, Britain is poorer than all but one American state.</li>
<li>Thereâs a <a href="//thenextweb.com/insider/2014/08/28/wales-tech-scene/">growing tech scene</a> in Wales.</li>
<li>Russiaâs biggest bank <a href="//www.businessweek.com/articles/2014-08-28/russias-biggest-bank-is-lending-cats%23r=rss">is lending</a> cats.</li>
<li>Walmart is <a href="//online.wsj.com/articles/wal-mart-looks-online-for-chinese-growth-1409249529?mod=rss_Technology">trying to grow online</a> in China.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Technology</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Appleâs iPhone 6, to be <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/apple-iphone-6-event-officially-set-for-sept-9/#f">unveiled</a> on Sept. 9, is expected to include <a href="//www.cnet.com/news/apples-new-iphone-6-expected-to-include-mobile-payments-nfc/">a mobile-payments platform</a>Â  powered by near-field communication.</li>
<li>Google is <a href="//bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/28/google-joins-amazon-in-dreams-of-drone-delivery/">testing delivery drones</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><em>Gene Marks owns the <a href="//www.marksgroup.net">Marks Group</a>, a Bala Cynwyd, Pa., consulting firm that helps clients with customer relationship management. You can follow him on <a href="https://www.twitter.com/genemarks">Twitter</a>.</em></p>
